1
00:01:53,375 --> 00:01:56,416
[laughing]

2
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:58,750
I still can't believe
that happened earlier.

3
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:00,375
After I busted my ass,

4
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:03,583
you made 19 flawless long-swords
like it was nothing.

5
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:05,250
[RIMURU]
They were only flawless

6
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,708
because they were copies
of your original.

7
00:02:07,791 --> 00:02:09,541
I just analyzed
your incredible work

8
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:12,083
and then used that
magisteel cluster to copy it.

9
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:13,666
Huh?

10
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:16,000
[RIMURU]
Sorry if that was out of line.

11
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:18,375
[MEN sigh]

12
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:20,333
[sighs]

13
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:24,208
Honestly, it is
a little frustrating.

14
00:02:24,291 --> 00:02:27,208
No matter, I suppose next time
I'll just have to make a weapon

15
00:02:27,291 --> 00:02:29,833
so amazing that even you
won't be able to copy it,

16
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:31,666
I'd relish a challenge.

17
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,750
[RIMURU]
That's the spirit!

18
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:36,583
And speaking of spirits,
refill please.

19
00:02:36,666 --> 00:02:39,541
Can you even taste this,
Mister Slime?

20
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:41,041
No, I can't.

21
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:43,333
But, hey, any drink is delicious
if it's being poured

22
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,250
by a pretty lady
such as yourself.

23
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:47,416
My, what a smooth talker.

24
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,958
Here. Enjoy.

25
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,916
[RIMURU] It's nice being on
this side of the entertaining.

26
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:57,916
In my old life, it was always me
pouring the drinks

27
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,708
and being overly attentive.

28
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:03,958
Ahh, this new life rules!

29
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Meanwhile,
Gobta had nothing to do

30
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,291
but hang out
back at the guard house.

31
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:11,291
[snoring]

32
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:12,500
[chuckling]

33
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:13,875
I'd love another.

34
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:15,916
Oh, hey. Mister Slime.

35
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,208
[RIMURU]
Huh?

36
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:19,958
Would you like to try
something special?

37
00:03:20,041 --> 00:03:21,083
[gasps]

38
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:23,083
[WOMAN]
This is a talent of mine.

39
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:26,125
In fact, everyone in town says
I'm the best at it.

40
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:29,333
Whoa! Shut up!

41
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,458
Is this what I think
it's going to be?

42
00:03:31,541 --> 00:03:33,708
[WOMAN moaning]

43
00:03:33,791 --> 00:03:35,666
[RIMURU]
When she says "special..."

44
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:38,125
[WOMAN moans]
Oh, my!

45
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:40,333
[RIMURU]
Is it that kind of special?!

46
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:42,333
Uh, really?

47
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:43,541
Like right here?

48
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:46,375
[gasps]
But, ma'am, people will see!

49
00:03:46,458 --> 00:03:47,416
[WOMAN]
Mister Slime?

50
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,291
[RIMURU]
We can't, we mustn't!

51
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:50,958
-[WOMAN] Mister Slime.
-[RIMURU gasps]

52
00:03:51,041 --> 00:03:52,333
So, are you ready?

53
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:54,333
[RIMURU yells]
Aw, man.

54
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:55,541
Fortune-telling.

55
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:58,708
What kind of things
can you see with that?

56
00:03:58,791 --> 00:04:00,208
Hmm.

57
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:01,833
Let's see.

58
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:02,958
Anything, really.

59
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:05,666
[sighs]

60
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,583
How about who he's
destined to be with?

61
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:09,166
-Huh?
-[ALL] Huh?

62
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,166
Hmm?

63
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:13,041
Yeah. Great idea.

64
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:17,291
Okay, here I go.

65
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:21,000
Ta-da!

66
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:23,250
Oh, no. I don't see anything.

67
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:25,041
-Aw.
-Hey!

68
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:26,291
[laughing]

69
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:27,666
I'm only teasing you.

70
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,166
I can't believe you fell for it.

71
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:30,583
[RIMURU]
Ugh. Meanie.

72
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:33,666
'Kay. I'm doing it
for real this time.

73
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:35,291
-[ALL] Huh?
-[MAN] Hmm?

74
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,916
Hmm?

75
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,875
[RIMURU sighs]

76
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:42,625
[RIMURU] The person
I'm supposed to be with.

77
00:04:42,708 --> 00:04:44,750
Is it possible I have
a soul mate here?

78
00:04:45,791 --> 00:04:49,250
Could there be a Missus Slime
waiting for me somewhere?

79
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,958
[FORTUNE-TELLER]
There, I see something.

80
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:52,041
[RIMURU gasps]

81
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,708
♪

82
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:04,833
[inaudible]

83
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:20,166
[RIMURU]
She kinda looked Japanese.

84
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,291
[KAIJIN]
Now that was a pretty lady.

85
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:23,208
[RIMURU gasps]

86
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:24,541
You're turning red.

87
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,083
Gah! I don't change colors.

88
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:28,958
Oh. I see.

89
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:30,916
Are you curious
about the girl you saw?

90
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,375
No fair.

91
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,333
What about me?

92
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:36,166
[RIMURU]
Of course I'm curious.

93
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:39,458
I wonder what she's like.

94
00:05:39,541 --> 00:05:41,083
If she's the one
I'm destined to be with

95
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,208
then I'd like to meet her.

96
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:43,875
[VESTA]
My, this is interesting.

97
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:46,333
Should you really be wasting
your time drinking?

98
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:47,916
Hmm.

99
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:51,166
Good evening, Kaijin.

100
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,291
Great, it's Minister Vesta.

101
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,208
[RIMURU]
Ah, so that's the guy.

102
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:59,250
He looks like somebody
wound his strings too tight.

103
00:06:02,041 --> 00:06:05,000
Honestly, I'm surprised
you're playing around like this.

104
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:07,000
Especially since the deadline
for those swords

105
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,083
is fast approaching.

106
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:09,708
I turned them in earlier.

107
00:06:09,791 --> 00:06:12,291
You know what will happen
if you don't finish them.

108
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,666
Wait. You're already done?

109
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,125
That's right.
With all 20 of them.

110
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,875
But that can't be.

111
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:23,125
It's true, you wanna
see the invoice?

112
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:26,500
[clears throat]
No, that's all right.

113
00:06:26,583 --> 00:06:27,833
Besides, finishing one's work...

114
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:29,625
[RIMURU] It feels like
this minister dude

115
00:06:29,708 --> 00:06:31,166
might have given Kaijin
what he thought

116
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,666
was an impossible order.

117
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,000
...doing your job...

118
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:35,916
[RIMURU] They don't seem
like they get along.

119
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,125
Honestly, I'm more concerned
with that creature.

120
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:40,166
[RIMURU]
Who? Me?

121
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,958
This is a nice place.

122
00:06:42,041 --> 00:06:43,666
I can't believe
you would have the audacity

123
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:45,541
to bring
that disgusting thing inside

124
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:47,166
and serve it like a guest.

125
00:06:47,250 --> 00:06:49,708
Just looking at it
makes me queasy.

126
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:52,500
So, since when do you
allow monsters

127
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:54,166
inside your establishment?

128
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,000
While it is a monster,

129
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,958
it's only a harmless
little slime.

130
00:06:58,041 --> 00:07:02,208
Yet, you do acknowledge
it is a monster.

131
00:07:02,291 --> 00:07:04,083
Or are you inferring
that because it's little,

132
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:05,000
it doesn't count?

133
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,333
No, it's not that.

134
00:07:07,416 --> 00:07:08,583
Really.

135
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:11,000
Here you are, Minister.

136
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:12,791
Have a drink, it's on the house.

137
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:14,458
Please. Enjoy.

138
00:07:15,708 --> 00:07:17,791
[scoffs]
Very well.

139
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:20,000
I'll show you
what this monster deserves.

140
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:22,416
-[ALL gasp]
-[WOMAN] Mister Slime!

141
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:26,166
[RIMURU]
Don't worry about me, I'm fine.

142
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,708
Did anything get on your dress?

143
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:29,000
[WOMAN]
A little.

144
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:32,208
[RIMURU sighs]
That really ticked me off.

145
00:07:32,291 --> 00:07:35,000
But the guy's a minister.

146
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:37,250
So I can't let my short fuse
screw things up

147
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,041
for Kaijin and this bar.

148
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,041
[GREAT SAGE]
Fruit wine.

149
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:43,125
Alcohol content
is seven percent.

150
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:45,666
[RIMURU] Thank you, Great Sage,
but this isn't the time.

151
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,375
-[grunts]
-[gasps]

152
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,750
-[grunts]
-[groans]

153
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,750
[ALL gasp]

154
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:54,500
Hey, Vesta.

155
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:56,791
Just because that monster
is more polite than you are

156
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:59,625
doesn't mean I'm willing
to let your insults slide.

157
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,916
You... You brute.

158
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
How dare you talk to a minister
in such a manner?

159
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,333
Shut up!

160
00:08:05,416 --> 00:08:07,750
-Kaijin.
-Go easy on him.

161
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:09,708
[RIMURU] Not in the face.
Aim for the body!

162
00:08:09,791 --> 00:08:11,125
[shudders]

163
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,750
[grunts]

164
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,583
[ALL gasp]

165
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:19,791
[RIMURU] Was it a good idea
to punch a minister?

166
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:21,666
I don't want you
to get into any trouble.

167
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,708
[KAIJIN]
Hey, Rimuru.

168
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:31,291
You said you needed
some skilled artisans, right?

169
00:08:34,458 --> 00:08:36,458
Think you can settle for me?

170
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:38,291
[RIMURU gasps]
Really?!

171
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:40,916
I don't need to settle
if I have you!

172
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,958
I'd be thrilled for you to help.

173
00:08:43,041 --> 00:08:44,291
Welcome aboard!

174
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:45,500
Hmm.

175
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,416
[RIMURU]
But this isn't a fairy tale,

176
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:53,125
so things rarely
work out so smoothly.

177
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,208
Come on now, bro.

178
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:57,708
Just what the heck
were you thinking?

179
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,583
Hmph!
He had it coming.

180
00:09:02,666 --> 00:09:05,041
That moron poured his drink
all over Rimuru,

181
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:08,416
and I decided it would be best
to teach him a little lesson.

182
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,583
A lesson, huh?

183
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:13,791
Look, you know you can't go
around assaulting a minister.

184
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:14,750
Hmph.

185
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,666
[RIMURU groans, sighs]

186
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,416
I don't have a choice here.

187
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,875
You broke the law.

188
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,625
I have to take you into custody.

189
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:22,916
You'll be detained
in the guardhouse

190
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,416
until the start
of your trial.

191
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,583
Guard.

192
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:27,416
Sorry about this,
it's not personal.

193
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,041
♪

194
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:33,916
[RIMURU]
Trial?

195
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,625
[groaning]

196
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:40,250
[exhales]

197
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,833
[inhales]

198
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:44,083
You've been asleep
this whole time?!

199
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,166
[sighs]

200
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,333
None of this would have happened

201
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:48,625
if I had just controlled
my temper.

202
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:51,208
What's worse is
I got you guys involved.

203
00:09:53,083 --> 00:09:54,041
Sorry.

204
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:55,375
Hey, it's okay.

205
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:56,833
Don't worry about it.

206
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,375
Seriously, there's nothing
to even apologize for.

207
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,625
Mm-hmm.

208
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:01,750
[RIMURU]
Say something!

209
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,958
Your brother said
something about a trial.

210
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:06,916
Yeah, don't worry about it.

211
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,750
Besides, it'll likely
end with a fine.

212
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,958
We won't get executed
or anything.

213
00:10:12,041 --> 00:10:13,208
[laughing]

214
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:15,583
[RIMURU]
I'm glad you can laugh.

215
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:17,250
Still, is there a reason

216
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:20,208
why that Minister Vesta guy
seems to have it out for you?

217
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:21,750
Hmm.

218
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:24,875
You see,

219
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:28,416
I used to work under this
nation's king, Gazel Dwargo.

220
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:31,250
I served as a captain
back in the palace,

221
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:34,875
over one of the seven orders
of royal knights.

222
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:37,041
At the time,
Vesta was assisting me

223
00:10:37,125 --> 00:10:38,875
as my second-in-command.

224
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:40,625
He was the son of a marquis,

225
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:42,458
and I came from
a family of peasants.

226
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:45,041
I'm sure it infuriated him.

227
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:48,125
Even back in those days,
we clashed constantly.

228
00:10:49,166 --> 00:10:50,791
And then...

229
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:52,791
[inaudible]

230
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:54,625
[crackling]

231
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:02,541
-[yelling]
-[gasping]

232
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:07,916
[KAIJIN]
One of the projects

233
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,333
that Vesta had been
under pressure to complete,

234
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:13,000
the Magisoldier Project...

235
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:15,041
went up in smoke.

236
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,500
Naturally, Vesta used me
as a scapegoat

237
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:20,375
for the project's failure.

238
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:22,250
He even bribed my forces,

239
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:25,000
using them to present
a false testimony.

240
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:29,791
So I had no choice
but to accept responsibility

241
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,375
and quit the force.

242
00:11:31,458 --> 00:11:34,125
These days,
he still has a grudge against me

243
00:11:34,208 --> 00:11:35,791
and tries to make
unreasonable demands

244
00:11:35,875 --> 00:11:37,166
at every opportunity.

245
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:40,083
That's what the sword thing
was about, too.

246
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:41,916
[RIMURU]
What a pathetic creep.

247
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,000
You're not wrong.

248
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:45,833
Still though,
if I'm being honest,

249
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:48,250
I really don't think
he's that bad a guy.

250
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,500
He and I had different ideas,
but he's a hard worker

251
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:53,750
and passionate
about his research.

252
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:56,375
The pressure he felt
to complete that project

253
00:11:56,458 --> 00:11:58,958
came from his desire
to please the king.

254
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:01,666
Me leaving this town
might be good for him,

255
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:04,291
perhaps he'll wise up
and move on with life.

256
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:06,083
[RIMURU]
We can only hope.

257
00:12:06,166 --> 00:12:09,541
Hmm. On that note, Rimuru,

258
00:12:09,625 --> 00:12:11,500
thanks for having me on board.

259
00:12:11,583 --> 00:12:13,041
[RIMURU]
Yeah.

260
00:12:15,416 --> 00:12:16,791
[GARM]
Now hold on a second.

261
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:19,583
If you want Kaijin,
then you gotta take us, too.

262
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:20,583
Hmm?

263
00:12:20,666 --> 00:12:21,791
He's right.

264
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:23,833
Anywhere Kaijin goes,
we'll follow.

265
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:24,833
We're a package.

266
00:12:24,916 --> 00:12:26,500
[RIMURU]
Huh?

267
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:27,500
Mm-hmm.

268
00:12:27,583 --> 00:12:28,500
[RIMURU]
Figures.

269
00:12:28,583 --> 00:12:29,875
Hmm.

270
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,541
Wow, you guys.

271
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:33,333
Well, Rimuru?

272
00:12:33,416 --> 00:12:36,541
Would we get in your way
too much if we tagged along?

273
00:12:36,625 --> 00:12:39,291
[RIMURU] Ha! I suppose I could
put up with you three.

274
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:41,625
But get ready, 'cause I'm gonna
work you to the bone!

275
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,541
-[BOTH] Right.
-Mm-hmm.

276
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:46,208
[ALL laughing]

277
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:49,750
[snoring]

278
00:12:58,208 --> 00:12:59,583
[RIMURU]
Interesting.

279
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:01,625
He doesn't make much sound
even when he's asleep.

280
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:03,333
[exhales]

281
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:06,333
Uh... Huh?

282
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:08,750
-[RIMURU] Huh?
-Uh, my lord?

283
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,458
Did something bad happen?

284
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:13,333
[RIMURU] I can't believe
he's just now noticed.

285
00:13:13,416 --> 00:13:15,458
We've got some
important things to do.

286
00:13:15,541 --> 00:13:16,708
Is it cool if you hang out here?

287
00:13:16,791 --> 00:13:18,208
Huh?

288
00:13:18,291 --> 00:13:20,166
I mean, if you wanna get out,
you should just call

289
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:21,791
your Tempest Wolf partner
or something.

290
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:23,541
Uh, hey, that's no fair!

291
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,291
[RIMURU]
Don't worry.

292
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:28,666
I probably won't forget to come
back for you when we're done.

293
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,750
[mumbling]

294
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:33,208
[RIMURU sighs]

295
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:36,458
Well, I don't wanna
drag Gobta into this trial

296
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,291
when he wasn't even involved.

297
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:43,375
♪

298
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:55,375
His Majesty, Gazel Dwargo,
will now enter.

299
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:58,291
♪

300
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:01,541
[groaning]

301
00:14:01,625 --> 00:14:02,583
[sighs]

302
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,000
[RIMURU narrating] The judge
presiding over Rimuru's party

303
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:19,583
is the Hero King
of the Dwarves, Gazel Dwargo.

304
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,416
Check out that guy's aura.

305
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:22,666
He's a beast!

306
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:24,208
No way I'd mess with him.

307
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:28,916
Everyone, we will now
begin the trial.

308
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,291
You may all rise.

309
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,875
[RIMURU]
This is me rising.

310
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,791
In the Armed Nation of Dwargon,

311
00:14:36,875 --> 00:14:39,000
no one is allowed
to speak during a trial

312
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:41,291
without the king's
express permission.

313
00:14:41,375 --> 00:14:42,666
For that reason,

314
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:45,083
a proxy is assigned
to speak for the defense.

315
00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:48,541
In conclusion, Minister Vesta
was minding his own business

316
00:14:48,625 --> 00:14:50,750
at the night club,
enjoying his drink.

317
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:53,583
Kaijin and his crew
entered the establishment,

318
00:14:53,666 --> 00:14:55,375
and they assaulted
the minister.

319
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:59,208
Such boorish behavior must not
be tolerated in our city.

320
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:02,125
Looks like he's been bought.

321
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,791
[RIMURU]
This sucks.

322
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,125
The guy is supposed to be
defending our case.

323
00:15:06,208 --> 00:15:10,125
Also, what's up with
all the extra bandages on Vesta?

324
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:12,375
And everything
you just stated is true?

325
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:13,541
Yes.

326
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:15,250
Beyond a shadow of a doubt.

327
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:19,916
King Gazel, now that you've
heard the proxy's testimony,

328
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,166
I request that you pass
your strictest judgment

329
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:23,708
upon these vagrants.

330
00:15:23,791 --> 00:15:25,375
[RIMURU]
Kaijin said he thought

331
00:15:25,458 --> 00:15:27,791
that Vesta wasn't
a bad guy deep down,

332
00:15:27,875 --> 00:15:30,500
but I gotta disagree
on this one.

333
00:15:30,583 --> 00:15:31,833
Please, sir.

334
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:36,000
[gavel pounding]

335
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:38,458
[ANNOUNCER] I will now deliver
the final verdict.

336
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,916
[RIMURU] Somehow I doubt
we'll get away

337
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,666
with just a measly fine.

338
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,625
I've got a really bad feeling.

339
00:15:44,708 --> 00:15:47,833
First off,
Kaijin, the main offender.

340
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:50,250
You are hereby sentenced
to 20 years

341
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,125
-of forced labor in the mines.
-[RIMURU gasps]

342
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:54,541
Next, I shall sentence
his accomplices.

343
00:15:54,625 --> 00:15:57,375
They will also serve time
doing forced labor,

344
00:15:57,458 --> 00:15:58,875
for the next ten years.

345
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,916
[RIMURU]
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

346
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,666
[ANNOUNCER] That is all,
the court is now adjourned.

347
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:06,291
[RIMURU]
Whoa. What just happened?

348
00:16:06,375 --> 00:16:07,583
-[GAZEL] Wait.
-Hmm?

349
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:09,041
[BOTH gasp]

350
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:13,875
It's been a while, Kaijn.

351
00:16:13,958 --> 00:16:16,041
Have you been well?

352
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:17,333
Sir.

353
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:19,708
[ANNOUNCER]
Speak, Kaijin.

354
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:21,041
Answer his majesty.

355
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:23,791
[KAIJIN]
Yes, I have been well, my lord,

356
00:16:23,875 --> 00:16:26,625
and I am relieved to see that
you are also in good health.

357
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,000
That's good to hear.

358
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,833
Are you at all interested
in returning to my ranks?

359
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:35,041
[gasps]

360
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:37,916
♪

361
00:16:42,625 --> 00:16:44,458
Forgive me, Your Majesty,

362
00:16:44,541 --> 00:16:47,333
but I have already
sworn myself to a master.

363
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:48,583
My word, and my oath

364
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:50,250
are the greatest treasures
I own.

365
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,958
And that's why,

366
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:54,083
I could never do anything
to forsake them,

367
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:55,958
even if you tried
to order me to do so.

368
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,500
[GUARD]
Insolence!

369
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,541
[RIMURU]
Whoa! Seriously?

370
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:02,875
♪

371
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:08,625
Right. I see.

372
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:15,625
I will pass my judgment.

373
00:17:15,708 --> 00:17:17,458
Kaijin and his companions

374
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:19,750
are hereby exiled
from this land.

375
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,291
That is my verdict.

376
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,833
Disappear from my sight at once.

377
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:29,041
[RIMURU sighs]
Exile I can totally handle.

378
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:33,291
Still, he seems a little a down.

379
00:17:35,583 --> 00:17:37,583
[sobbing]

380
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:39,750
[ANNOUNCER]
This court is now adjourned.

381
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,416
[door closes]

382
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:46,291
Right then, Vesta,

383
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:48,458
is there anything
you wish to say to me?

384
00:17:48,541 --> 00:17:50,750
Uh, me, sir?

385
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,250
Well, I...

386
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:54,000
No. Nothing.

387
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,000
How unfortunate.

388
00:17:57,083 --> 00:17:59,041
I am saddened by the fact
that I have lost

389
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:00,750
what I thought to be
a loyal retainer.

390
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:03,208
But how can you say
such a thing?

391
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:04,333
Kaijin, he...

392
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:05,916
He turned you down.

393
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,291
He swore his allegiance
to a slime monster.

394
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:10,875
He was never loyal to you,
he cares only for himself.

395
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:13,083
That's quite enough.

396
00:18:13,166 --> 00:18:15,166
I fear you've
misunderstood me, Vesta.

397
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:16,708
[gasps]

398
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:20,333
Kaijin isn't the loyal retainer
I've lost.

399
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:22,083
No.

400
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:28,041
[shudders]

401
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:32,458
[GAZEL] Once upon a time,
I had great hopes for you.

402
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:34,291
I waited for years

403
00:18:34,375 --> 00:18:36,958
after the failure
of the Magisoldier.

404
00:18:37,958 --> 00:18:40,875
I wanted the truth,
but I'm tired of waiting.

405
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,791
Uh, please, sir.

406
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,208
Your Majesty, I swear.

407
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,041
It's too late for excuses.

408
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,708
Look what he has.

409
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:51,833
[VESTA gasps]

410
00:18:51,916 --> 00:18:53,625
[GAZEL]
Do you know what that is?

411
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:56,333
It's a potion, a draft
of complete recovery,

412
00:18:56,416 --> 00:18:57,958
made from hipokute herbs.

413
00:18:58,041 --> 00:18:59,458
[VESTA]
It can't be.

414
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:02,625
Even with the most advanced
of dwarven techniques,

415
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:06,208
a potion can only achieve
98 percent recovery at the most.

416
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:08,833
How is this possible?

417
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:12,625
We received it as a gift,
from that slime.

418
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:14,166
[gasps]

419
00:19:16,666 --> 00:19:18,416
Now because of your actions,

420
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:21,041
we've severed our relationship
with that monster.

421
00:19:22,125 --> 00:19:24,791
Are you sure there's nothing
you'd like to say to me?

422
00:19:24,875 --> 00:19:26,541
[shudders]

423
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:30,666
No, sir.

424
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:33,916
I have nothing to say.

425
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,375
♪

426
00:19:40,375 --> 00:19:44,875
All I wanted was to be
useful to you somehow.

427
00:19:49,208 --> 00:19:52,208
Ever since I first saw you
when I was but a young boy.

428
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,416
It has always been my dream.

429
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:02,916
And yet I...

430
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,875
I've failed to do just that.

431
00:20:06,083 --> 00:20:08,125
All because I envied Kaijin.

432
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:11,875
Or was it something else?

433
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:17,708
For betraying
your great expectations,

434
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,458
I beg your forgiveness.

435
00:20:20,541 --> 00:20:23,208
[sobbing]

436
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:27,291
[GAZEL] Vesta, never
show yourself to me again.

437
00:20:27,375 --> 00:20:29,958
However, I do have
one last thing

438
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:32,083
I'd like to say
before you leave.

439
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,875
Thank you for your work.

440
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:40,958
[VESTA sobbing]

441
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,708
This is it.
Take care of yourself.

442
00:20:48,791 --> 00:20:50,958
Sorry for all the trouble.

443
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,333
You take care, too.

444
00:20:52,416 --> 00:20:54,000
Hmm.

445
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:56,583
Listen, Rimuru,
look after my bro.

446
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:59,333
[RIMURU] Don't you worry.
I'll only work him to death.

447
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:00,583
[scoffs]

448
00:21:02,166 --> 00:21:04,375
Now then, by order
of His Majesty,

449
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:07,791
Kaijin and his companions have
been exiled from this country.

450
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:09,625
You are to leave here at once.

451
00:21:25,416 --> 00:21:27,791
[RIMURU]
So, uh, shall we go?

452
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:29,916
My friends are waiting for us
in the forest.

453
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,250
Yeah.

454
00:21:33,458 --> 00:21:35,083
[RIMURU narrating]
Despite all that happened,

455
00:21:35,166 --> 00:21:37,041
Rimuru was able
to achieve his goal

456
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:40,500
of recruiting artisans
for the Goblin Village.

457
00:21:40,583 --> 00:21:43,791
What's more, he managed to hire
the most skilled artisans

458
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:45,708
that Dwargon had to offer.

459
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:49,250
♪

460
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:54,083
Have you apprehended the proxy?

461
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:56,416
-Punish him severely.
-[DARK AGENT] Yes, sir.

462
00:21:56,500 --> 00:22:00,166
And I want you to observe
that slime's movements.

463
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:03,208
It is unthinkable that we have
released such a monster.

464
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:07,208
Do not allow yourself
to be seen.

465
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:10,291
-No matter what.
-[DARK AGENT] Yes, sir.

466
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,041
That slime is too powerful.

467
00:22:16,916 --> 00:22:20,458
Its strength is on par
with the Storm Dragon Veldora.

468
00:23:52,916 --> 00:23:54,666
[GREAT SAGE]
Next time, "Shizu."

